election_record.label: Vermont 1823 Council

sub_unit.name: Addison
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original election returns report 1252 votes for Seth Wetmore, though the town votes in the original returns add up to 1332 votes.

sub_unit.name: Bennington
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original election returns list 254 votes for John Mason in Bennington County. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to 256.

sub_unit.name: Caledonia
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original election returns report 675 votes for Timothy Stanley, 641 for Joseph Berry, and 506 for John Aikin. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original election returns report no votes for John Roberts or John Mason in Essex County. The town votes in the original returns, however, yield 27 votes for Roberts and 100 for Mason.

sub_unit.name: Franklin
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original returns report 906 votes for Joel Pratt, 666 for Seth Wetmore, 793 for Truman Chittenden, 889 for Joseph Berry, 857 for John Roberts, and 53 for John Mason. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Orange
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original returns report 1054 votes for Truman Chittenden and 349 for John Aikin in Orange County. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Rutland
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original returns report 1480 votes for Joel Pratt, 1407 for Ezra Butler, 1411 for Israel R. Dana, 1299 for Timothy Stanley, and 1144 for John Mason. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Washington
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original returns list no votes for Jonas Clark, though the town votes in the original returns report 5 votes in Washington County.

sub_unit.name: Barre
sub_unit.note: John Roberts received 19 votes as Joseph Roberts.

sub_unit.name: Windham
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original returns report 1068 votes for Ezra Butler and 1070 for Seth Wetmore. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Windsor
sub_unit.note: The aggregate vote totals in the original election returns report 1126 votes for Joseph Berry, 587 for Sam H. Hotley, 603 for John Mason, 648 for Jonas Clark, and 236 for John Aikin. The town votes in the original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

election_record.reference: Original Election Returns. Vermont State Archives, Middlesex.
Woodstock Observer (Woodstock, VT), and Windsor and Orange County Gazette (Woodstock, VT). October 14, 1823.
